\title{rdtp: RD Tipping-Point Cutoff Search for Discrete Forcing Variables}
\description{
Searches over candidate cutoff values on a discrete running variable to find, for each unit, the cutoff that maximizes R-squared from a linear-spline regression discontinuity (RD) regression. Implements the threshold-detection method from McEachin, Domina, and Penner (2020, \doi{10.1002/pam.22202}) for settings where the true cutoff is unknown and varies across units (e.g., schools, counties). Supports OLS, heteroskedasticity-robust, and cluster-robust standard errors. Depends only on base R; robust/cluster SEs use 'sandwich' when available.
